description: 1981 Mercedes-Benz 380SLC 2 door hardtop coupe with a factory sunroof and heated rear window in absolutely beautiful condition throughout and boasting only 86K original miles, this model was by far most expensive model of the entire Mercedes line up of 1981, including all of the legendary Mercedes SL series, and which sold for an original MSRP of $47,853 ($127,254 CPI for 2016!) compared to $40,127 for the same year 380SL roadster!

The were sold as the C107 SLC coupe with the coupe model wheelbase lengthened by 14" to make room for the rear seat passengers in a fixed pillarless superstructure above the 2+2 cabin, whilst still incorporating its sports car dynamics. The 380SLC was built in very limited numbers in comparison with the roadster and was one of the most expensive and exclusive coupes ever made and which involved into the even more expensive and exclusive one year only and final year of production for the SLC model - the 1981 380SLC with only 3,789 built. These rare Long Wheel Base coupes offered the sensations of a true sports car but with the refinements of a four seater grand touring coupe!

description: For sale in our Dallas/Fort Worth showroom is a 1982 Mercedes-Benz 380SL. The SL name has always signified a certain level of quality and sophistication and the R107 model would be no exception. Introduced in 1972 year as a replacement for the W113 series, the 107 would make an unprecedented model run all the way through Ã¢??89. For me, these cars bring back very fond memories of my grandfather teaching me to drive around the neighborhood in his 380SL, which speaks volumes for the ease at which these cars can be piloted. This Ã¢??82 is a great example of an original well preserved 380SL. Owned by the same family since it was brand new, this little 380SL has been garaged and was part of their collection of several classic cars. This SL was usually driven on the week end to various outdoor car shows. The exterior is finished in the classic Mercedes White with blue leather interior. With the front engine rear wheel drive design handling characteristics are not quite what you would expect. The ride is plush yet stiff with the just the right amount road feel making it an absolute pleasure to drive. The interior is exactly what you would expect from a Benz. There is enough high quality leather to cover three sofas with the bucket seats being as comfortable as they look. The interior door panels are in great condition and definitely remind you that you are in a high end luxury car. With the late 70's and early 80's German cars being one of the hottest commodities in the collector car market this beauty is sure to find a new home quickly. Options on this 1982 Mercedes 380SL include AC, AM/FM/Cassette, Seat Belts, Power Steering, Power Brakes, Power Windows, Power locks, Power Windows, Power Seats, Tilt Wheel, Manual Convertible Top and Aluminum Alloy wheels with Radial Tires. To view this vehicle in greater detail including HD pictures and videos, visit www.gatewayclassiccars.com/carlist2?src=2&location=DFW&desc=Dallas. For additional information on this 1982 Mercedes-Benz 380SL, email us at dallas@gatewayclassiccars.com or call 817-310-9400.

description: Back in 1954, auto manufacturers were unveiling their new designs to the public at the New York auto show and this little roadster made a real impact on all that walked past. A few short years later, Mercedes-Benz started production of the 190SL for those who had been dreaming of the day they would be able to put that same car in their garage. Now after 60 years, this sleek black 190SL is back on a showroom floor and still dropping the jaws of all car enthusiasts that walk past. A beautifully restored Red interior, meets the driver as they gaze inside. A tan convertible top in excellent shape can be dropped back to enjoy the sunshine and get the full affect of owning such a unique roadster. This Mercedes was restored in 1996 and no expenses were spared in the restoration. All panels were smoothed and filled with lead (Old school style). The car was primed and worked until each panel was straight. The red interior is spectacular with detail given to every part of the restoration, from every knob to each screw head. Power brakes were added, along with an electric fuel pump for reliability. Seat belts were also added for safety. Since the work was completed, this car has been well cared for and looks just as great as it did all those years ago. Ã¢??A dream comes trueÃ¢?Â, was one of the slogans that Mercedes used when this car was new and the saying still is true today. This roadster is ready to be enjoyed and cared for by a new owner! This vehicle is located in our Milwaukee showroom. You can view this 1957 Mercedes 190 SL in greater detail including HD pictures and an HD video of it running and driving at Gatewayclassiccars.com. If you are interested in purchasing this vehicle or have more questions regarding it please call us at (262)-891-4253 or email us at Milwaukee@gatewayclassiccars.com.

description: Gateway Classic Cars of Philadelphia welcomes this classy 1978 Mercedes-Benz 450SEL to its showroom located in West Deptford, NJ!  The Sonderklasse or W116 Special Class first appeared on the automotive scene in 1972 and went on to represent a high standard for technologically advanced luxury vehicles. Modest, yet bold in its styling the Mercedes S-Class earned worldwide recognition in its appearance and continues to do so in the car community today. This dapper 1978 450SEL wears sharp coat of light blue metallic paint that pairs beautifully with the dark blue interior.  Take a seat inside and admire the handsome woodgrain panels that flow into a chique console that holds the AM/FM Radio with cassette, climate controls as well as the shifter that is linked to the automatic transmission.  Turn the key and watch the gauges come to life as the original 4.5 L M117 V8 engine purrs.  Equipped with power windows as well as a power sunroof, you should have no problem letting some fresh air in the cabin while you coast down the highway. Relax and wrap your hands around the steering wheel and know that you and your passengers will be comfortable and stylish in the original leather seats.  Style and luxury are not the only things that this Mercedes boasts as the W116 S-Class featured a number of safety innovations including a strengthened body structure, wrap around turn signals and a padded dash to reduce injury during impacts.  Additionally, one will note the factory bumpers with rubber mounts as per highway safety regulation from the mid to late 1970s.  This 450SEL has it all; luxury, technology and safety, seamlessly brought together by the legendary German manufacturer. Look no further for a beautiful classic import for this Mercedes-Benz is ready to roll! Additional features include Power Steering, Power Brakes and factory wheels. To view this 1978 Mercedes-Benz 450SEL in greater detail, including HD pictures and an HD video, visit www.GatewayClassicCars.com or our Philadelphia showroom located in West Deptford, NJ. For more information, please call 856-599-4100 or email Philadelphia@GatewayClassicCars.com
